metrics_conclusion: In terms of chords and melody, The Time (Dirty Bit) is more complex than the typical song, having above average scores in Melodic Complexity, Chord-Melody Tension, Chord Progression Novelty and Chord-Bass Melody.
key_conclusion:
The Time (Dirty Bit) is written in the key of E Mixolydian.  

According to the Theorytab database, it is the 2nd most popular key among Mixolydian keys and     the 26th most popular  among all keys. The E Mixolydian scale is similar to the E Major scale except that its 7th note (D) is a half step lower.  Mixolydian chord progressions are heavily featured in many genres of music like classic rock, which relies on the major chord built on the 7th scale degree. 

See the E Mixolydian Cheat Sheet for popular chords, chord progressions, downloadable midi files and more!

metadata.editComments: I left it in E Harmonic minor instead of D# minor to match with the E Mixolydian of the chorus. Rather this could be Hungarian minor scale and not Hmin: Because the IV note is sharp and the vii chord is d#m natural and not d# (diminished). However, in the vocals of the rapped part, the note D (bVII) hits a lot: Probably because of these dissonant but pleasant alterations they called it "Dirty Bit". Btw HookTheory really needs to add the 7 modes of the Hungarian minor scale (or the Byzantine Arabic), the Melodic minor, the 5 missing modes of the Harmonic minor and if possible also the modes of other rare scales like the Persian or the Neapolitans.
